<1ST_LINE>r w PM-ToyRecall     09-20 0187</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Toy Recall,180</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dolls, Rattles Recalled As Choking Hazards For Children</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Several small dolls and rattles marketed as
craft goods are being recalled by their manufacturer because they
could pose a choking hazard for children, the Consumer Product
Safety Commission has announced.
   The toys are being recalled by Fibre Craft Materials Corp. of
Niles, Ill., which said the products could be returned to the place
of purchase for a refund.
   Recalled rattles include ``Baby Rattle 4684,'' a noisemaking
blue ball atop a pink beaded handle; ``Plastic Spoon Decoration
4685,'' a pink, blue or yellow spoon with a painted-on face;
``Plastic Ball Decoration 4686,'' a blue and pink barbell; and
``Clothespin Cake Decoration 4687,'' a noisemaking blue clothespin
with a blue painted-on face.
   The dolls are being recalled because their arms may be pulled
off and possibly ingested by a child. They include ``Cupid'' dolls
numbers 3004, 3035, 3036, 3057, 3058 and 3220; ``Jill'' doll 3062,
``Beth'' doll 3086, ``Baby'' doll 3087 and ``Strawberry Girl'' doll
3101.
   More information can be obtained by calling Fibre Craft at
1-312-647-1140 or the Safety Commission at 1-800-638-2772.
</TEXT>
