<1ST_LINE>r p PM-Chairman'sMixup     09-20 0171</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Chairman's Mixup,0176</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Republican Chairman Mixes Up Governors at GOP Rally</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Republican Party National Chairman
Frank J. Fahrenkopf Jr. got his governors mixed up.
   At a GOP rally Monday, he introduced Florida Gov. Bob Martinez
as the governor of Texas and made Massachusetts Gov. Michael
Dukakis, the Democratic presidential candidate, the governor of
Florida.
   ``You've been traveling too much,'' Martinez said after
Fahrenkopf introduced him as the governor of Texas. Bill Clements
is the governor of Texas.
   ``I don't make mistakes like that, and I apologize for that,''
said Fahrenkopf, who then slipped again.
   ``I'm going to be in Texas, unfortunately, later in the day,''
he tried to explain.
   Fahrenkopf got Dukakis' state switched earlier while criticizing
the Democratic candidate's record as governor of Massachusetts.
   The GOP chairman was critical of a national television ad in
which Dukakis takes credit for balancing 10 straight budgets in his
home state.
   ``The facts are ... the constitution of the state of Florida
requires a balanced budget,'' Fahrenkopf said.
</TEXT>
