<HEAD>Wife Of Ambassador Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>THE HAGUE, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Patricia Pratt Shad, wife of U.S.
Ambassador John Shad, has died of cancer, the embassy said today.
She was 59.
   Mrs. Shad died Saturday, the embassy said. In addition to
cancer, she had been suffering from the after effects of a stroke,
according to an embassy source who spoke on condition of anonymity.
   Mrs. Shad was a graduate of the New York University Law School.
   Her 65-year-old husband was chairman of the U.S. Securities and
Exchange Commission until his appointment last year as ambassador
to the Netherlands.
</TEXT>
