<HEAD>Nude Jogger Becomes Burglary Suspect</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SMYRNA, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Midnight jogs in the nude around a high
school track apparently were just a warm-up for a man police
believe committed pre-dawn burglaries in his birthday suit.
   Late-night joggers reported seeing a nude man running at the
Campbell High School track about six weeks ago.
   A few weeks later, police said, early morning commuters on
Village Parkway spotted a man fitting the description of the jogger
wearing only his socks and tennis shoes.
   Lt. Edwin Clack Jr. said police began to suspect a relationship
between the incidents when they received a call about a nude
burglar.
   The man broke into a house in this Atlanta suburb early Saturday
but fled when he confronted by the woman who lived there.
   Police believe the same man was involved in all three incidents.
   ``We're anxious to get him off the street,'' Clack said.
</TEXT>
