<FILEID>AP-NR-09-20-88 1048EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Obit-Chambers     09-20 0158</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Chambers,0162</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Former Athens Publisher Dies at 46</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Robert W. Chambers Jr., former publisher of
the Athens Banner-Herald and the Athens Daily News, died today
after a short illness. He was 46.
   Chambers was president of Chambers Communications Consulting and
was a columnist for the Athens Observer.
   He became publisher of the Banner-Herald and Daily News in 1972
at the age of 29. He had joined the Banner-Herald as managing
editor in 1966 and became the newspapers' executive editor in 1969.
He left the papers in August 1985.
   A graduate of Emory University, Chambers became a copy editor
and later state editor at the Augusta Herald. He moved to Athens
when the Herald's parent company, Morris Communications Corp.,
bought the Athens newspapers in 1966.
   He was a past president of the Georgia Press Association and the
Athens Area Chamber of Commerce.
   He is survived by his father, R. Warde Chambers Sr. of Quitman.
</TEXT>
