<1ST_LINE>r w AM-MitsubishiRecall     09-20 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Mitsubishi Recall,130</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mitsubishi Recalls 100,000 Cars Due To Excessive Emissions</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mitsubishi Corp. is recalling 100,000 cars to
bring carbon monoxide emissions below federal standards, the
Environmental Protection Agency said Tuesday.
   The cars are the 1984 Dodge Colt, Plymouth Colt and the
Mitsubishi Precis, all equipped with the 1.4-liter (85 cubic
inches) engine, and the 1985 Dodge Colt, Plymouth Colt and
Mitsubishi Mirage, all equipped with the 1.5-liter (91 cubic
inches) engine. Models sold in California are not affected.
   The 1984 Precis was sold only in Puerto Rico.
   Dodge and Plymouth dealers will handle repairs to cars bearing
those names and Mitsubishi dealers will handle the cars bearing
their name.
   Dealers will modify the exhaust air injection system,
recalibrate automatic chokes, adjust the exhaust gas recirculation
system and, for the 1984 models, install a new carburetor main air
jet, EPA said.
</TEXT>
