``Hope it won't be long now.''
   McCarthy is one of 17 foreigners missing in Lebanon and believed
kidnapped.
   The others are nine Americans, two other Britons, an Irishman,
an Italian, an Indian and two unidentified men.
   Terry Anderson, chief Middle East correspondent of The
Associated Press, is the longest held hostage. He was kidnapped in
Beirut on March 16, 1985.
