<1ST_LINE>r a AM-First-Grader-Gun     09-20 0262</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-First-Grader-Gun,0270</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>First-Grader Brandishing Gun Apparently Demanded Sex from
Classmates</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAKELAND, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A first-grader on his way home from school
who allegedly pulled a gun on two female classmates and demanded
sex could be suspended for two years, a school official said.
   The 7-year-old boy, who told investigators he brought the gun
from home, was suspended immediately and awaits a hearing, said
Bill Duncan, who is in charge of discipline for the Polk County
school district.
   ``He did have a weapon there at the school and he did threaten
some girls with it,'' Duncan said. ``We know for a fact that he had
it because he admitted that he had it. Also, the mother admitted it
was her weapon, from the reports that I had.''
   ``At this point we have not charged him. We have not determined
that any violations have occurred,'' Polk County sheriff's
spokeswoman Lynne Breidenbach said Tuesday night. ``There's a big
if about whether charges will be filed.''
   The sheriff's report will be forwarded to the state attorney's
office for review, routine procedure in criminal investigations,
she said.
   School investigators don't know whether the gun was loaded. It
belonged to the live-in boyfriend of the boy's mother, Ms.
Breidenbach said.
   Authorities refused to reveal what kind of gun was used.
   The boy, whose name was being withheld, attended Crystal Lake
Elementary School. The incident occurred off school property, Ms.
Breidenbach said.
   Some classmates apparently saw the gun, but the boy threatened
them and told them to keep quiet, officials said. They told a
custodian after school.
</TEXT>
