<1ST_LINE>r a AM-`Nightmare'-Slaying     09-20 0228</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-`Nightmare'-Slaying,0235</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Say Man Killed Friend, Stole Car and Went to Movie</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HATFIELD, Wis. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man shot and stabbed his friend to
death, put the body in bed, stole the victim's car and went to see
a horror movie, police said.
   A child sat on the bed watching TV for hours without noticing
the body, police said.
   Bond was set at $250,000 Tuesday for Gary Thiede, 19, who was
arrested Monday night when authorities traced him to a small town
50 miles away, where he had gone to watch ``Nightmare on Elm Street
4: The Dream Master,'' said Jackson County Sheriff Gary Cummings.
   The victim, Robert Aponte, 16, was shot and stabbed about eight
hours earlier.
   Cummings said a baby sitter at Aponte's mother's house told
deputies she thought she heard a shot while Thiede was visiting but
did not investigate.
   When four children arrived home from school they thought Aponte
was asleep, the sheriff said. One sat on the edge of the bed and
Aponte's death went unnoticed for about four hours until his
stepfather called him to supper, Cummings said.
   Investigators were told two guns and the family's station wagon
were missing.
   Thiede was being held in Jackson County Jail in Black River
Falls pending a Friday hearing. District Attorney Jo Deen Lowe said
charges would include first-degree murder, burglary and theft.
</TEXT>
