<2ND_LINE>BC-Centel Buyback,0117</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Centel Buys Back Stock to End Takeover Threat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Centel Corp. ended a threatened takeover by a
group of New York investors when it bought back the group's stake
of 2.15 million shares of stock in the telecommunications company.
   Centel repurchased the shares for $43 each as part of a larger
buyback plan unveiled in June, it announced Monday.
   A member of the investment group, Metro Mobile CTS Chairman
George Lindemann, confirmed the group lost money on the aborted
takeover, but he wouldn't say how much.
   Lindemann and well-known arbitrager Asher Edelman had waged an
unsuccessful proxy fight for Centel, at one point offering $2.8
billion.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
