<HEAD>TRW Sells 2 Divisions</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BARTLESVILLE, Okla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   TRW Inc. announced Tuesday it has
agreed to sell two divisions to the British company Pearson PLC for
more than $300 million.
   TRW said in a statement it was selling its Reda Pump division,
based in Bartlesville, and its Oil Well Cable Division, based in
Lawrence, Kansas to Camco Inc., a Pearson subsidiary.
   The deal is expected to be closed within a few weeks, the
company said.
   Reda Pump has 800 employees nationwide, most of them in
Bartlesville, while Oil Well Cable has about 85 employees.
   TRW is involved in the defense, automotive and informations
systems businesses.
