<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street Noon,0375</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market posted a tiny gain today, but
the pace of trading was sluggish.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrial stocks, which fell 17.07
points on Monday, was up 1.78 points to 2,082.86 as of noontime.
   Advancing issues held a slim lead over declines on the New York
Stock Exchange, with 633 up, 610 down and 529 unchanged.
   Big Board volume totaled 70.58 million shares at noon on Wall
Street, compared with 69.80 million shares at the same point on
Monday.
   ``It's been pretty dull,'' said Charles Jensen, a technical
market analyst for the investment firm MKI Securities Corp.
   ``People are waiting for something more conclusive to stir them
off the sidelines,'' he said.
   The government's downward revision of its estimate of
second-quarter economic growth failed to provide any stimulus to
traders.
   Jensen noted that the report had virtually no impact on bond
prices, which often rally on indications of moderating economic
growth.
   At midday, Treasury notes and bond prices were trading close to
Monday's late levels.
   With bond yields still relatively attractive, Jensen said many
traders have found incentive to take the risks associated with the
uncertain returns on stocks.
   Among the blue chip issues, American Telephone & Telegraph was
up [ at 26], Exxon was unchanged at 45 and American Express fell {
to 28{.
   Kroger led the NYSE list of most most actively-traded issues,
slipping \ to 52{. The company said on Monday that the Haft family
had proposed at a takeover at $55 a share.
   Schlumberger rose 1} to 34. The oil-service company announced
late Monday that would repurchase 30 million shares of common stock.
   Time was down 8{ to 107}. The company said after the close of
trading on Monday that it isn't considering a leveraged buyout or
any other transaction. The company issued the statement after its
stock price had risen $19 a share over the past two sessions.
   Among the broader market indicators, the New York Stock Exchange
composite index of all listed issues rose 0.07 to 151.99. The
American Stock Exchange's market-value index rose 0.36 to 298.03.
